text.section:
The authorization agreement required by this section shall provide that:
on written notice, the authorized insurer may terminate at any time the authority of the reinsurance broker to act for it; and
the reinsurance broker shall:
render accounts to the authorized insurer detailing all material transactions, including information necessary to support the commissions, charges, and other fees received by or owed to the reinsurance broker;
remit all funds due to the authorized insurer within 30 days after receipt;
hold in a fiduciary capacity in a qualified financial institution all funds collected for the account of the authorized insurer;
keep all books, records, and accounts in accordance with § 8-514 of this subtitle;
comply with all written standards established by the authorized insurer for the cession or retrocession of all risks; and
disclose to the authorized insurer any relationship of the reinsurance broker with a reinsurer to which business is ceded or retroceded.
